title: Kit Rooney celebrates first birthday with a cute shoot | Daily Mail Online
text: Share 217 shares Enjoying the sumptuous cake topped with blue turquoise edible roses and striped candles, the little fellow looked like he was having a whale of a time. And another snap by Grace Kellie saw the tot enjoying a splash in a miniature blue rustic tub. Making memories: Proud parents Wayne, 31, and Coleen Rooney, 30, made the most of their youngest son Kit's milestone birthday, celebrating with a blue-themed photoshoot Clearly the cake became too tempting for the little one, as a cute photo caught him cheekily enjoying a slice of the cake. And ever the photogenic celebrity child, a final picture showed him proudly holding the colourful ballons, accentuating his bright blue peepers. Footballer Wayne and his wife Coleen were no doubt beaming with pride. Cutie: Surrounded by blue balloons and decorations, the adorable little tot posed in a cute bow tie and top hat emblazoned with the number 1 Last week Coleen shared a sweet family snap as they celebrated the milestone day. Taking to her Instagram page, Coleen posted a sweet snap of her, Kit, and her two other sons - Kai, 7, and Klay, three - clad in party hats and surrounded by balloons and presents. Excited to be celebrating such a milestone, Coleen captioned the shot: 'Happy 1st Birthday to our gorgeous baby Kit!' followed by a selection of heart emojis. Yum! Clearly the cake became too tempting for the little one, as a cute snap caught him cheekily enjoying a slice of the cake While Coleen, who began dating Wayne at age 16, often uploads family photos to her social media, she admitted she has developed a thick skin over the years - and stays strong in the face of negativity thanks to the love and support of her family. She explained to MailOnline earlier this month: ‘There’s so much criticism about how people look and their weight, but it’s never pressured me. I’m quite a strong character and I only ever do things for myself, not for anyone else. ‘From being in the public eye from a young age, that’s what I’ve learned. I’m quite confident now. Photogenic: Enjoying the sumptous cake topped with blue turquoise edible roses and striped candles, the little fellow looked like he was having a whale of a time Moving to warmer climates? Wayne could be considering a move to China to become one of the latest footballers to join the Chinese Super League ‘I’ve been lucky because me and Wayne have done it together, together we’ve [experienced] different negative things, I just think you’ve got to get on with it. This comes after it was revealed her husband, Wayne, could be considering a move to China to become one of the latest footballers to join the Chinese Super League. Coleen and Wayne raise three sons together; Kai, seven, Klay, three, and Kit, 1.
